‚ö†Ô∏è Complex conflicts are difficult on mobile.

8Ô∏è‚É£ Branch Operations (Basic)
Supported:

View branches

Checkout branches

Limited support:

Creating complex branch workflows

Rebasing

‚ö†Ô∏è Limitations of MGit
No built-in editor

Limited merge conflict resolution

Not suitable for large codebases

No CI / build execution

‚úÖ Best Practices for MGit
Use for documents & configs only

Keep commits small

Avoid rebasing on mobile

Sync frequently to avoid conflicts

üéØ Recommended Use Cases
Task	Suitability
README.md edits	‚úÖ Excellent
Documentation	‚úÖ Excellent
Daily logs	‚úÖ Good
Large code changes	‚ùå Not recommended
Complex merges	‚ùå Not recommended

üß† Key Takeaway
MGit is a mobile Git companion, not a full desktop replacement.
Use it for quick, safe, and lightweight Git tasks.

üìé This guide is ideal for:

Mobile documentation workflows

On-site logging and notes

Emergency Git fixes
